com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.storage

Class AdobeDesignLibraryUtils

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.storage.AdobeDesignLibraryUtils

  • public class AdobeDesignLibraryUtils
extends java.lang.Object
    A helper class that exposes methods to add specific type of elements to libraries and to get data from elements.

      • addImage

        public static AdobeLibraryElement addImage(java.lang.String imageFilePath,
                                           java.lang.String name,
                                           AdobeLibraryComposite library)
                                    throws AdobeLibraryException
        Adds an image element to the given library
        Parameters:
        imageFilePath - url of the source image to add to the new element. Local file url only is supported for now.
        name - name to use for this element.
        library - the library to which to add the new element.
        Returns:
        the new element
        Throws:
        AdobeLibraryException - if error occurs.

                                              AdobeLibraryComposite library)

        Parameters:

      • addRendition

        public static AdobeLibraryRepresentation addRendition(java.lang.String renditionFile,
                                                      java.lang.String contentType,
                                                      AdobeLibraryElement element,
                                                      AdobeLibraryComposite library,
                                                      java.lang.Integer width,
                                                      java.lang.Integer height,
                                                      boolean fullSize)
                                               throws AdobeLibraryException
        Adds a representation which is a ight for the given element.
        Parameters:
        renditionFile - the image file that is the rendition for this element. Local file URL is only supported in the current implementation.
        contentType - the content type of the given rendition file
        element - the element to add this this rendition representation to.
        library - the library which contains the given element.
        width - the width of the given rendition. (Optional)
        height - the height of the given rendition. (Optional)
        fullSize - whether or not the rendition represented with the path is full size. (Optional)
        Returns:
        the representation of the given element
        Throws:
        AdobeLibraryException - if error occurs.

      • getRepresentationTypesForElement

        public static java.util.List<java.lang.String> getRepresentationTypesForElement(AdobeLibraryElement element,
                                                                                AdobeLibraryComposite library)
        Returns the available representation content types for the given element.
        Parameters:
        element - the element for which to return the available representation content types.
        library - the library that contains the element.
        Returns:
        the unique list of available representation content types.

      • getImageFilePathForElement

        public static boolean getImageFilePathForElement(AdobeLibraryElement element,
                                                 java.lang.String contentType,
                                                 AdobeLibraryComposite library,
                                                 IAdobeGenericCompletionCallback<java.lang.String> completionCallback,
                                                 IAdobeGenericErrorCallback<AdobeLibraryException> errorCallback,
                                                 android.os.Handler callbackHandler)
        Returns the file URL for the given Image element and the content type.
        Parameters:
        element - the image element.
        contentType - the content type for the requested file.
        library - the library that contains this element.
        completionCallback - the completetion block that gets called with the file path in case of success.
        errorCallback - the error block that gets called in case of an error.
        callbackHandler - Optional parameter. If not null determines the operation queue completion and error blocks get executed on.
        Returns:
        false if this representation does not contain a file, otherwise true.
